---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Disaster911"
	description="Your trusted source for emergency preparedness and disaster response information"
	pubDate={new Date('November 07 2024')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		Disaster911 is your comprehensive resource for emergency preparedness, disaster response, and
		safety information. We are dedicated to helping individuals, families, and communities prepare
		for and respond to emergency situations of all kinds.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Mission</h2>
	<p>
		Our mission is to empower people with the knowledge, tools, and resources they need to stay
		safe during emergencies. Whether you're facing natural disasters like hurricanes, earthquakes,
		or wildfires, or preparing for other emergency scenarios, we provide reliable, actionable
		information to help you protect yourself and your loved ones.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Offer</h2>
	<p>
		Disaster911 provides a wide range of resources including emergency preparedness guides,
		disaster response protocols, safety checklists, and the latest updates on emergency situations.
		Our content is designed to be accessible, practical, and easy to implement, ensuring that
		everyone can benefit from our information regardless of their experience level.
	</p>

	<h2>Stay Prepared</h2>
	<p>
		Being prepared can make all the difference during an emergency. Through our blog posts, guides,
		and resources, we help you develop comprehensive emergency plans, build emergency kits, and
		stay informed about potential threats in your area. We believe that preparedness is not just
		about having supplies, but about having the knowledge and confidence to act when it matters most.
	</p>

	<h2>Community Focus</h2>
	<p>
		We believe that strong, prepared communities are more resilient in the face of disasters.
		That's why we emphasize community-based approaches to emergency preparedness and response.
		Together, we can build safer, more prepared communities ready to face any challenge.
	</p>
</Layout>
